			<node ID="ID_1860978386" TEXT="Advantages: 1. its a 56 bit key. So there are 2^56 possibilities of keys which would take a decade to find the correct key using brute-force attack 2. Encryption and decryption takes the same algorithm. Only that the function need to be reversed a" />
			</node>
		<node ID="ID_378451702" LINK="https://stackoverflow.com/questions/5257870/des-weak-keys" TEXT="c++ - DES. Weak Keys! - Stack Overflow">
			<node ID="ID_712219964" TEXT="A great crypto algorithm is worthless if the users use keys that are weak. DES is a wonderful example of this (among others) pitfall. That is something to be aware of even if you dont use DES to be sure to check the issue for the algorithms you do use. &#8211; littleadv Mar 10 11 at 9:56" />
