			<node ID="ID_1697587088" TEXT="A cryptographic hash function (CHF) is a hash function that is suitable for use in cryptography.It is a mathematical algorithm that maps data of arbitrary size (often called the message) to a bit string of a fixed size (the hash value hash or message digest) and is a one-way function that is a function which is practically infeasible to invert." />
