			<node ID="ID_519703689" TEXT="Message Digest 5 (MD5) is a hash function used in cryptography. Developed by Ronald Rivest in 1991 Message Digest 5 produces a 128-bit resulting hash value. Similar to other message-digest algorithms it was largely developed for digital signature applications which make use of a large compressed file in a secure fashion. Although it is still " />
